Notes / decisions:
  - Kept the same triggered_by='composio_webhook' value for poller-
    dispatched runs (rather than introducing 'composio_poll'). D.5's
    router already maps that to the composio_event lifecycle and the
    UI already renders it; introducing a new value would force a
    parallel cloud_runs.triggered_by enum widening + UI update with no
    behavioral difference.
  - sweep handler returns instead of throwing on missing
    COMPOSIO_API_KEY so EventBridge invocation history stays clean
    until F.3 actually registers an adapter and operator deploys.
  - Adapter framework lives in worker/src/poll-adapters/ (not worker/
    cron-kicker/) so future API-side code (e.g., F.9 trigger-registry
    initialState call) can import the same registry without depending
    on the kicker bundle.
